Belgium centre-back, Jan Vertonghen’s current deal expires next summer and he will be free to speak to foreign clubs in January as things stand. READ ALSO:  Arsenal and Manchester United keen on Atlanta United’s Ezequiel Barco Vertonghen, who has been of interest to Roma and Bayer Leverkusen, was also open to holding talks over an extension under previous manager Mauricio Pochettino – and he was told he was not for sale in the summer. The formal discussions between Chairman Daniel Levy and Vertonghen’s representatives is yet to take place.